{"questionId":"19198","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Points in the plane are subjected to a transformation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi></math> in which the point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>)</mo></math> is transformed to the point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>'</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>'</mo><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp;where</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mtable><mtr><mtd><mi>x</mi><mo>'</mo></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>y</mi><mo>'</mo></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>3</mn></mtd><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd><mtd><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mtable><mtr><mtd><mi>x</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>y</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Show that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A'&nbsp;B'&nbsp;C'&nbsp;D'</mtext></math>&nbsp;is a parallelogram.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>Grad&nbsp;A'B'</mtext><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>8</mn><mn>9</mn></mfrac><mo>;</mo><mtext>&nbsp;Grad&nbsp;C'D'</mtext><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>8</mn><mn>9</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>therefore&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A'B'</mtext></math>&nbsp;is parallel to&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>C'D'</mtext></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>Grad&nbsp;A'D'</mtext><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>6</mn><mn>12</mn></mfrac><mo>;</mo><mtext>&nbsp;Grad&nbsp;B'C'</mtext><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>6</mn><mn>12</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>therefore&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A'D'</mtext></math>&nbsp;is parallel to&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>B'C'</mtext></math></p>\n<p>therefore&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A' B' C' D'</mtext></math>&nbsp;is a parallelogram&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><br>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"19198","referenceCode":"20N.1.AHL.TZ0.F_7b.iv","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Show that A' B' C' D' is a parallelogram.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b.iv","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.9—Matrix transformations"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}